The cheese of the pizza is out of this world and don't get me started on the pepperoni. The only bad thing about this place is the customer service. Excellent pizza with great prices and an awesome variety of dishes to please even the most fussiest eaters in your household. They have been around since the early 1980's serving the Little Village community and they have been doing this by expanding not only their facilities and locations, but their menu as well. My favorite is the "Nova Special" with tomatoe slices instead of green pepper. Their broasted chicken and hot buffalo wings are a close second favorites. They also have catering for all of your personal, corporate and private events. They also have their own delivery service in place and ready to serve a large area in Chicagoland. If you're in the area give them a call or stop by and enjoy some of the best pizza in Chicago.

I realize some people have complained about the price of the food; however, they are suppose to be getting fresh and organic ingredients, and some vegetables have gone up on the market due to the pandemic. I usually get the Vegetarian Pizza, Onion Rings and Coleslaw. I think the food is absolutely delicious. I have only had it home delivered so I cannot comment on picking up. But the delivery was fast, within the time they said it would be and the delivery guy was very friendly. From their menu, they also offer other things such as salads, sandwiches and a variety of chicken wings. I give them a thumbs up for high quality food.
